Stockton.Rancho Campo de los Franceses: Rancho Campo de los Franceses was a 48,747-acre (197.27 km2) Mexican land grant in present day San Joaquin County, California given in 1844 by Governor Manuel Micheltorena to Guillermo Gulnac. "Campo de los Franceses” which in English means “French Camp” refers to French-Canadian fur trappers who wintered there. The grant included present day French Camp and Stockton.
